21/03/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The 15th anniversary of the first Macedonian government following independence from the former Yugoslavia was marked in Skopje on Monday (20 March). In a public statement, former Prime Minister Nikola Kljusev said the 23-member cabinet, which included academics and other non-party figures, had worked to set the foundations of an independent Macedonia.
In other news Monday, the four Macedonian Albanians kidnapped and killed by the Taliban in Afghanistan last week were buried in their home country -- three in Tetovo and one in Skopje. They had been working for a German company, Ecolog. (Macedonian Government Web site, Albanian News - 21/03/06; A1 TV, Dnevnik, Makfax, A1 TV - 20/03/06)
